The paper is analyzing the literature on Natural Language Processing (NLP), which is a subfield of Computer Science. The focus is on the ACL Anthology, which is a digital repository of NLP articles. Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also mentions the use of machine learning techniques (cs.DL - Digital Libraries, cs.LG - Learning), information retrieval (cs.IR), and inclusiveness in research (cs.SI - Social and Information Networks).
